<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: IDENTITY_LINKED_VARIABLE_CORRELATION
@GOAL: DETECT_HARDCODED_CREDENTIALS_BY_MAPPING_VARIABLE_NAMES_TO_DISCOVERY_ASSETS
@PARENT_CONTEXT: identity_model.protocol, data_inventory.protocol, authentication_strategy.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
SEMANTIC_DICT: {
  "AUTH": "(password|passwd|pwd|token|secret|key|access|credential)",
  "DATABASE": "(db_pass|connection_string|pg_password|database_url)",
  "ADMIN": "(admin_val|root_access|su_pass)",
  "PROVIDER_SPECIFIC": "(aws_key|stripe_secret|sendgrid_api|vault_token)"
}
NOISE_FILTER: "(example|placeholder|dummy|test_user|your_password_here)"
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<ASSERTIONS>
! ([VAR_NAME] ~ [SEMANTIC_DICT] && [VAR_VALUE] == "LiteralString" && ![VAR_VALUE] ~ "^process\.env") : "CRITICAL: Hardcoded Credential."
</ASSERTIONS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. AST_TOKEN_EXTRACTION: Анализ дерева кода (AST) для поиска VariableDeclarations.
2. SEMANTIC_FILTERING: Сопоставление имен переменных с [SEMANTIC_DICT].
3. DISCOVERY_CORRELATION: Проверка, используется ли данный провайдер в проекте согласно [KNOWN_PROVIDERS] из Discovery.
4. IMPACT_ASSESSMENT: Оценка, куда передается переменная (Sinks) — в БД, Лог или Внешний API.

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [identity_variable_correlation]:
FILE: [PATH]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [VAR_NAME] = [VAR_VALUE]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: An attacker with access to the source code or binary can extract the static credential to bypass authentication on the [ASSET_NAME] service.
VISUALIZE: "Image of code AST tree highlighting nodes where sensitive variable names are assigned to literal strings."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>